authorizeMiddleware(address).details: register an authorized middleware so that modifier onlyIbcMw can be used to restrict access to only authorized middleware. Only the address with the IBC_ROLE can execute the function.

onERC721Received(address,address,uint256.details: Whenever an {IERC721} `tokenId` token is transferred to this contract via {IERC721-safeTransferFrom} by `operator` from `from`, this function is called. It must return its Solidity selector to confirm the token transfer. If any other value is returned or the interface is not implemented by the recipient, the transfer will be reverted. The selector can be obtained in Solidity with `IERC721Receiver.onERC721Received.selector`.

onRecvUniversalPacket(bytes32,(bytes32,u.details: Packet lifecycle callback that implements packet receipt logic and returns and acknowledgement packet.      MUST be overriden by the inheriting contract.

params._channelId: the ID of the channel (locally) the packet was received on.
params.packet: the Universal packet encoded by the source and relayed by the relayer.

onTimeoutUniversalPacket(bytes32,(bytes3.details: Packet lifecycle callback that implements packet receipt logic and return and acknowledgement packet.      MUST be overriden by the inheriting contract.      NOT SUPPORTED YET

params._channelId: the ID of the channel (locally) the timeout was submitted on.
params.packet: the Universal packet encoded by the counterparty and relayed by the relayer

onUniversalAcknowledgement(bytes32,(byte.details: Packet lifecycle callback that implements packet acknowledgment logic.      MUST be overriden by the inheriting contract.

params.ack: the acknowledgment packet encoded by the destination and relayed by the relayer.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setDefaultMw(address).details: Set the default IBC middleware contract in the MW stack. When sending packets, the default middleware is the next middleware in the MW stack. When receiving packets, the default middleware is the previous middleware in the MW stack.

params._middleware: The address of the IbcMiddleware contract.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

authorizeMiddleware(address).notice: Should add this modifier to all IBC-related callback functions.

setDefaultMw(address).notice: The default middleware is authorized automatically.
